sense.name: the exercise of control over something
sense.examples: This year's loss of the championship ended their team's six-year domination of the sport. Thirty years of domination by a dictator had dismantled most of the nation's social institutions. Wolf packs are hierarchical with the top wolf maintaining domination over all the other wolves.

sense.name: the fourth (of nine) ranks in the celestial hierarchy of angels
sense.examples: The dominations were the angels dwelling in the fourth region of the celestial hierarchy.
